ly</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   PoN Trio</span><hr size=1> Here's a nice setup that I've played around with. Seems to work great.<br>
<br>
60 Mage (me)<br>
60 Enchanter<br>
58 Ranger<br>
<br>
We set up camp just north of the Graveyard<br>
<br>
Ranger pulls one of the arachnids, enchanter charms it. The enchanter will be tempted to direcharm a bat, but don't do it! Stick with regular charm. Arachnids seem to work best, too.<br>
<br>
Then the ranger goes off and chainpulls. Meanwhile the charmed spider tanks the mob, while mage pet (60 water in my case) beats it senseless and the mage lets loose with nukes. When the charmed spider breaks charm, enchanter can recharm it. And when the charmed spider gets much too low on HP, well lets just say you have an easy target :P<br>
<br>
The trick is to ensure the charmed pet has all the aggro and the mage pet has none. PoN mobs hit HARD and will rip through a mage pet fast. Too many adds can be a problem if the enchanter can't mez them all safely, or if charm breaks at the worst possible time.<br>
<br>
Considering this is yard trash we've been killing, the exp is phenomenal. But the pulls have to be fast and constant. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=terrato686>Terrato686</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 3:02:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoN Trio</span><hr size=1> This would work great as long as the chanter doesn't die trying to recharm the pet while it aggros her when the charm breaks. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://daggerspath.net/images/EQWebGraphics/Terrato.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 754<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 4:26:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoN Trio</span><hr size=1> Heh, I have done PoN with just a mag partner....  it was actually pretty silly because the partner didn't have IR.  I'd send pet in, and so would he... we'd chain the mob til the mob was dead.  That worked until the other magician (WITH KEI) started running LOM.  At that point we changed the strategy to basically me soloing the mob, with him sending his pet in between reclaims, then backing out once my new pet was up and fighting.  It worked pretty nicely.<br>
<br>
I'd like to try some tougher mobs with an IR partner but magicians who use that skill are few and far between...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cerilin>Cerilin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 10:03:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=319.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoN Trio</span><hr size=1> I duo here all the time and occassionaly allow a lower lvl ench friend I know to tag along, I am lvl 59 with epic atm, and i partner with a lvl 62 druid all the time.  What we do is let the druid charm a bat or a WW.  I turn pets taunt off, ds the charmed pet, wait a second sick pet on whatever mob.  Is extremely easy, except when charm breaks for the druid, but we try to keep the charmed pet snared, makes it a little trickier but still easy as pie.  We bring the ench along to slow occassionaly and than we TEAR mobs apart faster than the can spawn.<br>
