<br>
56 Mage (me)<br>
61 Druid<br>
57 Ranger<br>
<br>
<br>
Between the two of them, they were able to keep all the ones that spawned away from the rocks rooted with no problem. The druid would charm one (if she had trouble getting it to stick, I would send my air pet in long enough for a stun to go off. that always did the trick <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) then sick it on one of the rooted ones along with my pet as the ranger fired arrows and I nuked (I summoned about 300 of them before we started and ended up having to summon more about an hour into it.) <br>
<br>
This worked quite nicely. I walked away with 2 yellows and 3 blues of normal XPs (getting my level in the process. Yay!) and a yellow of AAXPs in the span of about 2 and 1/2 hours. (we took 2 15 minute breaks) <p><p><center><font face="MS Sans Serif"><b>***************************************</b>
